  "prompt": "Why was I blocked from adding questions on quora anonymously and how can I change it?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you were blocked from adding questions anonymously on Quora. Some common reasons include:\n\n1. **Violation of Guidelines**: Quora has strict community guidelines, and if any of your past content violated these rules, it might have led to a block on certain features.\n\n2. **Suspicious Activity**: If Quora detects unusual activity from your account, such as posting spam or rapidly posting similar questions, it might temporarily restrict access to some features.\n\n3. **Spam Detection**: Automated systems might have flagged your account if your questions were considered spammy or inappropriate.\n\n4. **User Reports**: Other users might have reported your anonymous questions, leading to a restriction.\n\nTo address this issue, you can try the following:\n\n1. **Contact Quora Support**: Visit Quora\u2019s help center and submit a request explaining your situation. Be polite and provide any relevant details that can help them understand and resolve the issue.\n\n2. **Review Guidelines**: Re-read Quora\u2019s community guidelines to ensure you understand the rules and ensure that your past content adhered to them.\n\n3. **Use Your Profile**: Temporarily posting questions using your profile might be a workaround if anonymous posting is restricted.\n\n4. **Wait and Try Again**: If the block is temporary, sometimes waiting a few days can resolve the issue as restrictions are lifted naturally after some time.\n\nEnsure that any future content, whether anonymous or not, complies with Quora's community standards to prevent further restrictions.",
